HEADWORD: Sleeky
<hw>Sleek"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of a
sleek, or smooth, and glossy appearance.</def>
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fawning and deceitful; sly.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

